Was so saddened to hear of Buck Henry’s passing yesterday. I remember the joy I felt every morning when I was on the way to work with Buck on the pilot of Get Smart. He could break me up with just a screwy look on his face. He was a truly great comedy writer who will be missed.
Happy to share the good news that the original comedy SAM directed by my son @nickbrooks72 is now available to watch on Amazon, FandangoNow, Vimeo, and Vudu!

And after you have watched the show there’s more! @HBO has put two of my previous comedy specials back on @hbogo and @hbonow - “Mel Brooks And Dick Cavett Together Again” and “Mel Brooks Live At The Geffen”

Neil Simon was a clutch hitter. When we needed the punchline on Your Show of Shows he delivered. He also delivered 32 plays and over 20 movies. He was one of the sweetest & least jealous writers you could ever work with. For all who knew him, this is a truly sad day.

So sad to hear of the passing of my dear friend and gifted choreographer Alan Johnson. He created that unforgettable Springtime for Hitler number in my first movie, The Producers. He shall be sorely missed. He was one of a kind.
